==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Hydroxylamine
<hw>Hy*drox`yl*am"ine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Hydroxyl</ets> + <ets>amine</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A nitrogenous, organic base, <chform>NH2.OH</chform>, resembling
ammonia, and produced by a modified reduction of nitric acid. It is
usually obtained as a volatile, unstable solution in water. It acts as a
strong reducing agent.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>hydroxymethyl</ent>⟦br⟧
